DESCRIPTION
Amazon is seeking a Senior Manager Public Policy to be either based in Munich or Berlin.

Would you like to be part of a public policy team focused on increasing awareness and adoption of Amazon Web Services (AWS)* and the utility cloud model at the public sector and healthcare industries market segments in Germany and Austria? Do you have significant government affairs experience and have the information technology public policy knowledge necessary to help further advance AWS as a leading cloud platform provider at the country and regional level in Germany?

AWS is the leading provider of cloud computing services, providing IT infrastructure offerings such as on-demand compute capacity, storage, content delivery, database services and more. We are looking for a talented, innovative, and well-connected individual to represent AWS in Germany and Austria, before policymakers that are strategically important to the AWS public sector and healthcare business. The successful candidate will proactively build relationships with key policymakers, IT decision makers and executives in government and other relevant organizations and help prioritize federal and regional government public policy issues faced by AWS. You will address policy risks to the business as well as advance strategic initiatives in these market segments. This position will also be involved in AWS’s participation in key business associations and coalitions that are critical to advancing AWS public policy and business objectives. You will become familiar with all aspects of AWS’s business, and interface directly with the business units in the region. This government affairs and policy position shall:

- Develop, lead and implement government affairs advocacy objectives and policy/political priorities for AWS in Germany and Austria;
- Represent key positions directly and through industry associations/coalitions to national governments in Germany to enable an unrestricted, transparent and technology friendly regulatory environment within healthcare and public sector for the growth of AWS.
- Work collaboratively and transparently with the AWS public sector business units and other Amazon teams to ensure alignment between core business priorities, public policy goals and “go to market” strategies;
- Assess and communicate potential regulatory threats and government sector market segment (revenue) opportunities and threats, develop mitigation or enhancement strategies and policy positions, and coordinate external advocacy efforts, outreach programs and key initiatives in concert with AWS business objectives;
- Facilitate high-level meetings between AWS executives and key stakeholders, including senior government officials, regulators, industry association and alliance partners to promote and advocate the company’s public policies;
- Determine, maintain and staff appropriate corporate membership opportunities in industry associations/coalitions on behalf of AWS, and ensure appropriate utilization of high judgment, high integrity outside consultants.

The successful candidate must be inquisitive, enthusiastic about technology, enjoy working hard and being continually challenged, and demonstrate sound judgment even in ambiguous situations. The responsibilities require that candidates be willing and able to make frequent trips across Germany, Austria and, as needed, to Brussels, London, Luxembourg, Seattle and other locations.

DESCRIPTION
Our Munich-based team is looking for an innovative, hands-on, and customer-obsessed Recruiter to join our Worldwide Consumer Talent Acquisition team, supporting hiring for Consumer businesses in Germany. This person will be responsible for partnering with senior customers and other stakeholders to hire the very best talent to our growing teams.


Responsibilities include:
· Providing first-class recruiting support for internal customer groups in Munich, Berlin and other EU locations;
· Operating as the expert in industry best practices for all functional areas of recruitment, monitoring new trends and opportunities to consistently raise the standard for recruitment at Amazon;
· Proactively sourcing, building awareness of the very best passive candidates and creating a "talent bench" for future hiring;
· Providing internal resourcing consultancy service to hiring managers, including the provision of advice on all recruitment issues;
· Managing the recruitment process from initial candidate contact to offer ensuring an outstanding candidate experience;
· Analysing and implementing process improvements;
· Developing creative and effective sourcing strategies and plans to build pipelines for top candidates across all areas of the organization, working with recruiting team colleagues to develop and execute tactical sourcing strategies and with our Brand Manager on raising awareness of Amazon as a great place to build a career;
· Screening, assessing and qualifying candidates against Amazon’s Leadership Principles
· Scaling sourcing methodology and tools to meet growing appetite for passive candidate attraction techniques within the business;
· Working to promote our culture of diversity and inclusion both internally and externally.

DESCRIPTION
Description

Amazon’s vision is to be Earth's most customer-centric company; to build a place where people can come to find and discover anything they might want to buy online.

Amazon's diverse online business requires VAT filings in a number of jurisdictions across Europe and creates specific VAT compliance obligations relating to third parties (3P) that sell via our websites. These 3P obligations are the responsibility of the European VAT Compliance & Controllership team (VAT C&C) which is located primarily in London and Bratislava. We are looking for an energetic and enthusiastic 3P Compliance VAT Administrator to join our VAT C&C team in Munich. The role will involve working within the part of the team that is responsible for checking the VAT compliance status of our 3P sellers, providing 3P data to tax authorities, and controlling the access of 3P sellers to our websites. Work may also include some mainstream VAT compliance activities, supporting internal and external audits, and liaising with colleagues in VAT C&C as well as Tax and the wider business – you will need an understanding of financial systems, and technical accounting awareness for this work. You may also be involved in projects that have a VAT compliance impact. You will be expected to take ownership of your activities, identify process improvement opportunities for existing process and controls, and drive positive change across the organization. One of the main responsibilities will be to handle all the communication, via Fax, phone and emails, with German Tax offices and maintain good relationship with these Tax offices.

Responsibilities:

Working within the EMEA VAT C&C team:
· Confirm the VAT registration and compliance status of 3P sellers;
· Provide transactional and other data to tax authorities in respect of 3P sellers;
· Manage and control access of 3P sellers to Amazon marketplaces based on VAT compliance status and requests from tax authorities;
· Assist with VAT registrations across various jurisdictions;
· Respond to VAT compliance queries from Amazon businesses operating across Europe;
· Provide internal and external audit support, including data analysis;
· Provide support to colleagues throughout the business and, in particular, accounting groups;
· Participate in cross-functional projects;
· Actively map VAT compliance processes and identify areas for improvement;
· Communication with German tax offices
· Ensure proper and professional relationship with Tax offices is maintained

DESCRIPTION
Our European Procurement team is growing and we are hiring a MHE Category Manager with Pan-European responsibilities to join the team in our European Headquarters in lovely Luxembourg.
As a MHE Category Manager, you will create and own the strategic relationship with suppliers and senior internal stakeholders while building collaboration within and across organizational boundaries. You will develop key sourcing activities, ensuring equipment and service availability to meet business goals while minimizing risk. You will be the trusted advisor in strategic sourcing and procurement initiatives. You will work side-by-side with your stakeholders to deliver the best end customer experience.

RESPONSIBILITIES

· Develop and deliver long term sourcing strategies, supervise key initiatives with cross-functional teams; promote the process of the category roadmap with regional senior leadership;
· Define commercial relationships with suppliers, with a principal objective of achieving optimal cost and performance;
· Supervise supplier performance management including improving sustainability & social responsibility;
· Coordinate and collaborate with local teams to deploy and handle the implementation of your defined strategies.

LEARNING OPPORTUNITIES

· Autonomy to innovate and deliver new approaches that impact the bottom and the top line;
· Grow in a fast-pace environment where every day is day one;
· Being surrounded by inspiring and diverse employees;
· Learn from people with a wide variety of professional backgrounds;
· Ability to develop new skills and opportunities through lateral, geographical or functional moves.

DESCRIPTION
Amazon Web Services (AWS), a leader in cloud computing, is seeking a curious, highly-intelligent, self-motivated and creative communications, marketing, and change management professional who is looking to apply their skills and experience in innovative ways. This role will be responsible for delivering high quality service to AWS' growing Public Sector Professional Services team and cover the Europe, Middle East, and Africa (EMEA) and Asia, Pacific, and Japan (APJ) practices.

AWS’ growth is driving a rapid expansion of its world-wide sales team and there is an increased need for support in communications, intranet platforms, training materials, marketing development, and change management within the Professional Services team that supports their work. This includes enhancing our existing communication channels and discovering new digital innovations that enable us to make real-time updates, provide topical messages, and link our employees (past, present, and future) to the information they need and want to know. The successful candidate must be able to manage multiple tasks simultaneously, and thrive in a dynamic environment while continually evaluating whether prevailing strategies are delivering the impact needed to justify their time and effort across different customer populations. The ideal candidate would have several years in communications, marketing, or capabilities development, and have strong written and verbal communication skills.

This is an opportunity for a creative, dynamic, and results-driven communications professional to add significant value to the AWS Public Sector Professional Services team.


Key areas of responsibility

· Create communications content that drives engagement with our AWS employees;
· Translate business needs into offerings and communications materials;
· Proactively build and manage relationships with key internal stakeholders across a range of businesses and geographies;
· Responsible for the creation of creative internal content and digital content;
· Coordinate production and localization of content to better serve the needs of the regional teams;
· Listen and bring awareness to online chatter (including across all intranet sites and inside existing tool platforms), then connect people to resources, escalate questions, comments or concerns coming from our employees;
· Monitor and measure the effectiveness of communications through digital analytics, surveys, and other key performance indicators;
· Review and manage existing content libraries to determine opportunities to improve the learning and communications experience for our employees, ensure the content is current, relevant and that the best technology platform is used.

DESCRIPTION
Amazon is a leader in global e-commerce. We’re working to be the most customer-centric company on earth. Our innovative technologies change the way people find, discover and buy products and services. Lawyers at Amazon are trusted members of the business. Our work is intellectually challenging, exciting and fast-paced. Developing innovative solutions to novel legal questions is part of our daily business. Like everyone at Amazon, we’re passionate about our customers.

Amazon`s Legal Department is looking for an experienced Employment Lawyer to support our German corporate businesses as well as our German customer service, customer fulfillment and transportation operations. You will be the primary point of contact for the dedicated HR teams and work on a broad range of individual and collective employment law related issues. You will also provide day-to-day labor and employment law advice to our management teams and be responsible for the design and roll-out of trainings to non-legal teams. As part of Amazon´s German Legal team based in Munich you will work on exciting projects across business lines and across the EU, dealing with a variety of employment law topics and providing strategic counsel.


You must have excellent organizational skills and be a strong written and verbal communicator, with great attention to detail. You will need to be able to work independently in a constantly changing and sometimes ambiguous and complex environment. You also need common sense, great judgment, and a sense of humour. This position involves direct contact with business owners and external parties. We are looking for candidates who are innovative, progressive, extremely hands-on, and customer-obsessed professionals. In addition, they must be proactive and fast-moving when necessary to complete projects in a timely fashion.


Your responsibilities:
· Advising and supporting the HR teams on all German labor and employment related matters, such as disciplinary proceedings, health and safety, performance management, consultation;
· Training the HR and Recruiting teams on new legislation, develop and implement forms and processes and help simplify automate processes;
· Advising the businesses on strategic matters, including hiring and talent management strategy;
· Drafting and implementing employment policies and standard documentation in close cooperation with the HR teams and stakeholders across the EU;
· Reviewing and drafting of works agreements with works councils;
· Proactive planning, advising and implementing legal and compliance programs and improvements to support and protect the business;
· Handling administration and resolution of issues arising in existing relationships as well as pre-litigation disputes;
· Responsibility of employment litigation management including outside counsel management;
· Supporting the businesses in dealing with relevant regulatory issues
